metadata.title: Boeing-Stearman Model 75
aws::graph::propositions: Variants of the Boeing-Stearman Model 75 formed the PT-17 family.
Stearman 76 was an export trainer version of the Boeing-Stearman Model 75.
Stearman 76 was an armed version of the Boeing-Stearman Model 75.
Stearman 76 featured one or two fixed forward firing machine guns.
A76B4 was a variant of the Stearman 76.
Five A76B4 aircraft were built for Venezuela.
A76C3 was a variant of the Stearman 76.
Fifteen A76C3 aircraft were built for Brazil.
B76C3 was a variant of the Stearman 76.
Fifteen B76C3 aircraft were built with cameras for Brazil.
76D1 was a variant of the Stearman 76.
Sixteen 76D1 aircraft were built for Argentina.
Three 76D1 aircraft were built for Philippines as BT-1.
S76D1 was a seaplane version of the 76D1 for Argentina.
76D3 was a variant of the Stearman 76.
Twenty-four 76D3 aircraft were built for Philippine Constabulary as BT-1 armed advanced trainer.
Twenty-four 76D3 aircraft were built for Cuba.

text:
Variants of the 75 formed the PT-17 family.
Stearman 76
Export trainer and armed version of the 75 with a gun ring and one or two fixed forward firing machine guns.
A76B4
5 built for Venezuela.
A76C3
15 built for Brazil.
B76C3
15 built with cameras for Brazil.
76D1
16 built for Argentina and three for Philippines as BT-1.
S76D1
seaplane version of 76D1 for Argentina
76D3
24 built for Philippine Constabulary as BT-1 armed advanced trainer, and 24 built for Cuba.
